    "content" : "<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_bounce.gif\" alt=\":bounce:\" title=\"bounce\"> Evening all \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_bounce.gif\" alt=\":bounce:\" title=\"bounce\"> \n<br>\n<br>Up at what I thought was early only to realise we'd lost an hour \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif\" alt=\":roll:\" title=\"Roll Eyes\"> \n<br>\n<br>After breakfast I decided to have another look at the flasher / hazard system, but first I got some paint on the gearstick spacer\n<br>\n<br>With a bit of heat in the cave it soon dried. The hazards have got me flummoxed \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif\" alt=\":?\" title=\"Confused\"> It's not a problem, everything works but I just wanted it modified a bit. I need to have a beer with an auto electrician into VW buses \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> So, having failed, I put the gearstick in. I'm happy with it and it works well. What it's like to drive with, time will tell. Still, another job ticked off \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> \n<br>\n<br>Painted\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3012_zpsyyk5o99a.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3012_zpsyyk5o99a.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Installed\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3013_zpsygbsat2t.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3013_zpsygbsat2t.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Finished. Hopefully the carpets will cover most of the spacer anyway\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3014_zpsg2tk75zk.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3014_zpsg2tk75zk.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Dad came around for an hour or two and he brought with him a woodruff key. We'd manage to shear a couple in the Vespa and I read on the 'net last night that this was probably due to not torquing up the flywheel enough. A possibility as I'd only used my hand to hold it. We made up a flywheel holding tool, torqued it up to setting FT and I kicked it over………….started first time \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> I even had a little ride round the drive \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> Dad disappeared for lunch with us both being fairly pleased with ourselves. \n<br>\n<br>This, not running, wreck \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Motovespa/DSCN0466_zps32f91179.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Motovespa/DSCN0466_zps32f91179.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>to this working stable mate for Rusty. Nearly but not quite finished.\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Motovespa/IMAG3007_zpsk75qlhjd.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Motovespa/IMAG3007_zpsk75qlhjd.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Next up wasRusty's petrol tank. We tested the sender unit, prior to fitting the tank in the bus \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\"Wink\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\"Wink\"> \n<br>\n<br>Sender unit not connected\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3015_zpspgxnksj2.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3015_zpspgxnksj2.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>and with the sender connected the gauge moved up to \"zero.\" Something appears to be working \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> I've fitted a voltage dropper from AHS at the moment but was able to buy from Peter Good his last electronic voltages dropper/stabiliser so I may fit that later on, depending on the performance of the gauge…. \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3016_zps9wvspn9w.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3016_zps9wvspn9w.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>The outlet was sealed with the old outlet nut and a bit of fishpond rubber and then I poured in some fuel\n<br>I was going to use water but this would have meant draining and leaving for a day to dry out so we opened all the doors and stuck in 5 litres of petrol \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_eek.gif\" alt=\"8O\" title=\"eek\">\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3017_zpsehqywswo.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3017_zpsehqywswo.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>The gauge moved a little, but then I had only put a little fuel in. Not wanting to decant 30 or so more litres of fuel in the cave I got the Sheila to help…. \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3018_zpsizkygkwa.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3018_zpsizkygkwa.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>I turned the tank over. Bingo! The gauge went to full.\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3019_zpsrbmnzt6d.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3019_zpsrbmnzt6d.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>So with that test having been successful, I made some rubber mounting pads up for the tank….more fishpond rubber \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif\" alt=\":roll:\" title=\"Roll Eyes\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3020_zpsifmpyvfu.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3020_zpsifmpyvfu.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>All prepped for the install\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3021_zpsdoe2mrab.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3021_zpsdoe2mrab.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Mary gave me a hand so that we didn't scratch anything and the tank went in reasonably easily after a little twisting and turning so I dug out the neck rubber…..but which way does it go????\n<br>\n<br>Like this? I don't think that's right as it would collect the fuel…..\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3022_zpsdfrsq19c.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3022_zpsdfrsq19c.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>or like this? This was my bet…..but I'm not good at betting \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif\" alt=\":lol:\" title=\"LOL\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3023_zpsr59m94q8.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3023_zpsr59m94q8.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>I couldn't find it in Bentley \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_eek.gif\" alt=\"8O\" title=\"eek\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3024_zpsg5aaa7hp.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3024_zpsg5aaa7hp.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>but C &amp; C's exploded diagrams came to the rescue…….again…. \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3025_zpsmdez2zt4.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3025_zpsmdez2zt4.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Here's a little tip….put a washer with a big hole underneath the strap…..that way it won't chip the paint when it twists as it tightens….like it did on mine \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> More touch up required…..\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3026_zpsp2ycvs2z.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3026_zpsp2ycvs2z.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>After a while it was done. I used some rubber to soften the corners a little but it also hides the fact that the paint chipped off in layers where the straps are bent. Probably better to pre bend the straps prior to painting \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_evil.gif\" alt=\":evil:\" title=\"Evil\"> Oh well, next time \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif\" alt=\":lol:\" title=\"LOL\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3027_zpscgqzrvms.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3027_zpscgqzrvms.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>Sender wires all clipped in……\n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3032_zpsx6fn5lxo.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3032_zpsx6fn5lxo.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>and fuel cap fitted \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_cheers.gif\" alt=\":cheers:\" title=\"cheers\"> \n<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://s790.photobucket.com/user/stevejones3163/media/Rusty2/IMAG3028_zpsqeicgsvu.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i790.photobucket.com/albums/yy185/stevejones3163/Rusty2/IMAG3028_zpsqeicgsvu.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br>\n<br>What next????? Suggestions…. I'm thinking the fuel pump and solenoid fit…\n<br>\n<br>Over and out.\n<br>\n<br>Steve",
